graph_desc.gtype_area_default: Overlapping areas show values. Use to show spikes in data.
graph_desc.gtype_area_percent: Area show percentage of total. Use to show change in percentage over time.
graph_desc.gtype_area_split_dualy_stacke: Stacked areas show cumulative values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_area_split_dualy: Overlapping areas show values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_area_stacked: Areas are stacked on top of each other, showing cumulative totals for each group.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_default: Each row show a value. Use to show trends or to compare values.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_dualy_stacked: Bars are stacked to show cumulative totals. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_dualy: Groups of bars a values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_floating_stacked: Bars rise above or below a baseline. Use to show the flow of positive and negative trends in data.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_percent: Bars show cumulative percentages. Use to show change in percentage over time.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_split_dualy_stacked: Bars are stacked to show cumulative totals. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_split_dualy: Groups of bars a values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_bar_stacked: Bars are stacked to show cumulative totals. Use to show trends and relationships at the same time.
graph_desc.gtype_combination_default: Combines bars and lines, bars and areas, lines and areas, or all three.
graph_desc.gtype_combination_dualy: Combines bars and lines, bars and areas, lines and areas, or all three and shows values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_default: Each row show a value. Use to show trends or to compare values.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_dualy_stacked: Bars are stacked to show cumulative totals. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_dualy: Groups of bars a values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_percent: Bars show cumulative percentages. Use to show change in percentage over time.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_split_dualy_stacke: Bars are stacked to show cumulative totals. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_split_dualy: Groups of bars a values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_hbar_stacked: Bars are stacked to show cumulative totals. Use to show trends and relationships at the same time.
graph_desc.gtype_line_default: Lines to show values. Use to show trends or to compare values.
graph_desc.gtype_line_dualy_stacked: Lines show cumulative totals. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_line_dualy: Lines to show values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_line_mix_frequency: Lines show values whoose locations along with the horizontal Time axis are variable. Time locations for the diffenent lines are not synchronized.
graph_desc.gtype_line_percent: Lines show cumulative percentages. Use to show change in percentage over time.
graph_desc.gtype_line_split_dualy_stacke: Lines show cumulative totals. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_line_split_dualy: Lines to show values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_line_stacked: Lines show cumulative totals. Use to show trends and relationships at the same time.
graph_desc.gtype_pareto_default: Bars show values that make up a whole; a line show the cumulative percentage of the whole that the bars so far comprise. Use to identify sources or causes of defects.
graph_desc.gtype_pie_bar: Pie graph, with extra detail for one slice. Detail appear in stacked bar that is connected to the slice.
graph_desc.gtype_pie_default: Use to show percentage of total.
graph_desc.gtype_pie_multiple_ring: Use to show percentage of multiple totals.
graph_desc.gtype_pie_multiple: Use to show multiple percentages of multiple totals.
graph_desc.gtype_pie_ring_bar: Pie graph, with extra detail for one slice. Detail appear in stacked bar that is connected to the slice.
graph_desc.gtype_pie_ring: Use to show percentage of total. The total pie appears in the hole in th center.
graph_desc.gtype_scatter_default: Location of each data point shows 2 values. Use to compare 2 values that each have many values.
graph_desc.gtype_scatter_dualy: Location of each data point shows 2 values. Use to compare 2 values that each have many values. Each Y-Axis can use a different scale.
graph_desc.gtype_scatter_polar: Circular scatter graph. Use to show data that is directional in nature.
